Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.16,0:00:05.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, Asseylum Vers Allusia,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.58,0:00:09.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,will take Count Slaine Saazbaum\NTroyard as my husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.54,0:00:14.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and proclaim that I shall create\Na new kingdom here in Earthspace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.13,0:00:19.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At this time, in spite of the best efforts\Nof you daring and resolute knights,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.46,0:00:23.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}this war is giving every indication\Nthat it will become protracted.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.51,0:00:27.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With matters having come to this,\Nwhat should our course of action be?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.26,0:00:30.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this a time for Orbital Knights\Nto squabble among themselves?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.18,0:00:33.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is it a time to compete \Nfor one's own glory?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.98,0:00:41.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The time has come for us to gather under one\Nflag and fight together for the future of Vers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.11,0:00:48.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have delegated all of my authority to the\Nlord of this newly empowered castle,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.62,0:00:53.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and my future consort, Count Troyard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.25,0:01:06.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This includes the right to decide upon whom\Nto bestow the power to awaken Aldnoah.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.47,0:01:09.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Until the day comes\Nwhen we achieve victory in this war,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.97,0:01:15.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it is my heartfelt wish that you think of\NCount Troyard's words as my own
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.81,0:01:17.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and rally to his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.32,0:01:21.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All that we do, we do for Vers!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.58,0:03:04.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The battle against Earth\Ncontinues to prove difficult, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.55,0:03:09.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milord. But to those knights\Nwho are anxious regarding this situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.18,0:03:13.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness's words must have\Nbeen akin to divine revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.72,0:03:14.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Divine revelation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.85,0:03:20.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone knows that she was only able to\Nissue that proclamation because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.56,0:03:24.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To the knights who are unhappy\Nabout the present state of affairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.11,0:03:25.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,they were words from on high.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.86,0:03:29.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely they must feel that someone\Nhas appeared who will lead them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.78,0:03:33.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You exaggerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.45,0:03:38.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But on the other hand, rebel factions\Nare also certain to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.16,0:03:40.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is something that I wish\Nyou to do on that front.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.83,0:03:44.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Make a display of power? \NIs that what you mean, Milord?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.54,0:03:48.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, if we continue to engage with such ilk,\Nwe will never see the end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.67,0:03:51.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Start by rooting out the\Ndangerous elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.01,0:03:53.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can let the proper authorities\Ntake it from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.72,0:03:54.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.80,0:03:57.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum's name\Nwill be motivation enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.60,0:03:59.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it should be simple enough
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.02,0:04:01.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to strip them of their knighthood\Nwith some random accusation or other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.23,0:04:06.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You do not approve?\NYou think it too underhanded?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.15,0:04:08.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, Milord. Quite the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.15,0:04:12.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is only natural that you would stop\Nat nothing to achieve your goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.28,0:04:15.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since the announcement, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.91,0:04:19.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I may be so bold,\Nyou seem to have firmed your resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.21,0:04:27.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My wish was to be close to Her Highness.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.50,0:04:30.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My wish was to be worthy of her.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.97,0:04:34.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And to be of some service to her...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.51,0:04:36.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.02,0:04:44.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If power is the only thing \Nthat I can achieve, then...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.73,0:04:48.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Harklight? Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.15,0:04:51.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,M-Milord Slaine...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.36,0:04:56.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Eddelrittuo?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.16,0:05:02.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are quite satisfied with\Nyour ship's current actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.90,0:05:07.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the time being, we want you to continue\N providing unit support as a commando squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.09,0:05:10.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no objections to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.17,0:05:13.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But with regard to the proclamation\Nby Princess Asseylum...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.08,0:05:16.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That nonsense about founding\Na new dynasty in Earthspace?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.68,0:05:20.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing but big talk meant\Nto stir up the Mars Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.22,0:05:21.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We doubt it's anything more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.98,0:05:23.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That might be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.60,0:05:27.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But perhaps we should consider\Nthe possibility that the enemy's attacks
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.73,0:05:29.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,may escalate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.40,0:05:33.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're sitting on our thumbs, doing nothing?\NIs that what you are implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.53,0:05:37.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, sir. I meant nothing of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.62,0:05:42.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As far as new operations go, we are currently\Ncoordinating with our primary units.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.87,0:05:46.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once that has been finalized,\Nyou will be contacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.83,0:05:50.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You may be unhappy with your\Nstatus as a commando unit,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.75,0:05:54.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but there is no telling how much faith we can\Nput in a ship that runs on enemy technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.34,0:05:57.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not to put too fine a point on it,\Nbut that's just how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:05.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed that you sat through\Nthat without any outbursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.73,0:06:10.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you want me to?\NRemember, I'm only here as your escort.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.36,0:06:12.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm not that naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.07,0:06:15.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They just don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.03,0:06:20.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They probably just don't know what they've got.\NThey're doing the best they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.99,0:06:25.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'm not griping about\Nhow they're treating the Deucalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.91,0:06:27.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But they're being overconfident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.75,0:06:28.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.38,0:06:30.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, about the Martians.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.25,0:06:34.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The war may have tilted \Never so slightly in our favor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.30,0:06:37.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but it does not justify \Ntheir possibly misguided optimism.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.33,0:06:39.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I find the prospect terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.60,0:06:49.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will drain the therapeutic fluid and\Nbring Princess Asseylum to my castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.65,0:06:50.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell no one of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.94,0:06:54.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not even Princess Lemrina, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.44,0:06:55.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But why not—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.15,0:06:55.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do as I say!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.95,0:07:02.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me. I did not mean to startle you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.87,0:07:06.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No visitors allowed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.67,0:07:12.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My sister's condition is that serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.42,0:07:16.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She... Perhaps it was a miracle\Nthat she held on for this long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.05,0:07:21.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How much time does she have?\NToday? Tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:23.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They say that they still do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.47,0:07:27.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is just as possible that she will remain\Nin this condition indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.43,0:07:29.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.44,0:07:31.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can guess what you are feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.40,0:07:36.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You may have mixed feelings, but she\Nis your only sibling by blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.94,0:07:40.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is you who are truly sad,\Naren't you, Slaine?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.62,0:07:44.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.74,0:07:46.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.08,0:07:51.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I forgive you, Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.33,0:07:56.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you cry in front of me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.13,0:07:58.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you shed tears over her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.55,0:08:01.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.05,0:08:05.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...am already yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.64,0:08:16.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Could that have triggered it?\NNo... It couldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.03,0:08:20.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I always looked up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.36,0:08:24.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You had everything that I did not.\NSo I hated you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.12,0:08:30.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, do not worry, sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.96,0:08:34.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, I will officially \Ntake your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.20,0:08:39.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will be Slaine's support!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.72,0:08:45.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.38,0:08:59.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's up with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.78,0:09:01.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean she got ditched here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.65,0:09:05.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"The captain left me in charge\Nbecause she trusts me."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.07,0:09:10.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what she said, but Cdr. Mizusaki\Nhas got to be devastated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.50,0:09:13.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did she pick Lt. Marito of all people\Nas her traveling companion?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.79,0:09:16.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Companion? Escort, more like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.33,0:09:18.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about Lt. Marito?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.92,0:09:23.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, um... It's just that he accompanied\Nthe captain to the conference,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.47,0:09:25.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought it might be serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.43,0:09:31.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. With that Martian proclamation and all,\Nthe situation is definitely in flux.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.47,0:09:34.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that the princess\Nis getting married...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.26,0:09:36.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you're interested in?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.06,0:09:37.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, but look...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.86,0:09:43.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it possible that her change of heart was\Nbecause of someone she developed feelings for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.15,0:09:46.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like, she was seduced by him or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.15,0:09:47.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.37,0:09:53.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we're still not 100% sure that\Nthe Princess Asseylum who said that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.87,0:09:55.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,was the princess who\Nspent time with us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.25,0:09:58.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I honestly can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.59,0:10:02.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho insists that she is an impostor,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.26,0:10:06.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no telling\Njust how much even he can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.51,0:10:08.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you eaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.47,0:10:14.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In a bit. Let me find\Na good place to leave off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.64,0:10:17.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've been this way since we were little.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.35,0:10:19.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you're into something,\Neverything else fades away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:20.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.48,0:10:22.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.74,0:10:28.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard, right? About Asseylum's, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.03,0:10:29.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.37,0:10:34.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That proclamation seemed to prove\Neverything you've been saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.33,0:10:39.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It all seems a little too convenient, and if that\Nreally were the genuine Princess Asseylum,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.74,0:10:44.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,would she think of a founding\Na kingdom in Earthspace?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.92,0:10:48.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine Troyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.05,0:10:52.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That douchebag who shot\Nmy dear little brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.39,0:10:57.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. But watch your language, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.23,0:11:02.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter if she's\Nreal or not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.07,0:11:05.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think anyone would listen to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.03,0:11:11.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she tried to broker a peace\Nbetween Earth and Mars again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.54,0:11:15.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About the attack on Earth, Milord,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.95,0:11:18.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if there are no problems,\NI will get preparations underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.67,0:11:23.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Slaine?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.00,0:11:26.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm listening. Proceed as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.05,0:11:29.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milord. Her Highness has yet to—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.59,0:11:31.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She will wake up soon. I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.97,0:11:35.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I eagerly await that day, Milord.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.22,0:11:36.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.06,0:11:38.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But... the thought also terrifies me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.29,0:11:38.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.19,0:11:41.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.82,0:11:50.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Has there been any change?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.03,0:11:54.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. They believe that she might remain\Nin this condition for some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.58,0:11:58.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will wait as long as it takes.\NWe are used to waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.08,0:12:04.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She will surely be surprised, waking up\Nto find that everything has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.92,0:12:07.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.84,0:12:10.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will I seem different to her, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.43,0:12:16.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She will think that you have grown\Ninto a fine man, I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.19,0:12:21.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall return.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.91,0:12:34.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Slaine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.74,0:12:37.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...rittuo...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.79,0:12:40.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Eddelrittuo...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.37,0:12:41.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milady...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.79,0:12:44.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.63,0:12:49.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She... She is awake...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.42,0:12:52.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness! It is me! It is Slaine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.39,0:12:59.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you recognize me?\NIt's Slaine, Slaine Troyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.18,0:13:04.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am Slaine Troyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.53,0:13:16.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.99,0:13:22.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine... Slaine... Slaine...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.01,0:13:28.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine... Slaine... Slaine...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.88,0:13:30.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.21,0:13:39.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting so long to hear you\Nsay my name once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.52,0:14:29.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let me begin by saying that I am glad\Nto see you safe, Count Mazuurek.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.90,0:14:33.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies for causing you\Nto worry, Count Barouhcruz.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.44,0:14:34.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So, what are your plans?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.11,0:14:39.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have none as yet. I have lost\Nmy Kataphrakt, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.70,0:14:43.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you wish to ally yourself with Count\NTroyard, I can act as intermediary.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.33,0:14:47.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have heard what happened\Nwith Count Marylcian.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.37,0:14:49.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been most galling.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.38,0:14:54.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, both sides fought fairly,\Nand that was the result.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.05,0:14:55.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is nothing to hold a grudge over.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.42,0:14:59.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Barouhcruz,\NTroyard is dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.55,0:15:02.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He not only killed Marylcian,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.39,0:15:04.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there are even suspicions that\Nhe also killed Count Saazbaum—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.93,0:15:08.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who spoke of such accusations?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.56,0:15:11.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I merely... But you—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.86,0:15:16.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hold your tongue. How could you let yourself\Nbe misled by such unfounded rumors?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.66,0:15:22.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You heard Princess Asseylum's\Nproclamation, I take it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.45,0:15:26.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one can stop Count Troyard's rise.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.50,0:15:30.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not when he holds all the cards,\Neven Aldnoah activation privileges.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.83,0:15:33.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As they say, "Do not try to fight\Nan Olympian sandstorm."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.59,0:15:39.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you wish to make a comeback,\NI suggest you choose wisely.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.26,0:15:45.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Barouhcruz pledges his full\Nand unconditional cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.35,0:15:50.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Counts Sebring and Raffia have have\Nyet to make their allegiances clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.73,0:15:53.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but they appear to be amenable to\Nacknowledging the new kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.23,0:15:57.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Morale is also on the increase\Nwithin the base.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.82,0:16:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have almost finished compiling
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.78,0:16:03.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the list of knights who\Nseem likely to oppose you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.07,0:16:06.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are ready to take the necessary \Nsteps by force at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.25,0:16:08.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Slaine?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.71,0:16:12.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.54,0:16:18.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Begging your pardon, Milord, but is it\Nabout Princess Asseylum's recovery?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.59,0:16:25.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to give her time off? Eddelrittuo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.64,0:16:29.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. If only a little while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.35,0:16:34.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum's sudden turn \Ncame as quite a shock to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.69,0:16:41.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I shouldn't wonder. And how are\Nyou taking it, Slaine? I've been worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.66,0:16:44.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.99,0:16:49.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are the only person\Nthat I can count on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.71,0:16:52.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will make Vers mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.50,0:16:55.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For Her Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.14,0:17:15.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dales Platoon and Orlov Platoon currently\Nmarching towards enemy Landing Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:20.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Clydesdale and Mustang commando platoons,\Nbe on alert for enemy Kataphrakts,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.24,0:17:24.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and once one's spotted, go on the offensive\Nimmediately and destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.04,0:17:34.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.33,0:17:39.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Lord Slaine had this garden\Nmade for you, Milady.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.80,0:17:41.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he did?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.26,0:17:45.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks just like Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.32,0:17:49.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It does. Are your memories of Earth returning?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.98,0:17:59.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Birds...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.90,0:18:02.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was watching birds... with that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.74,0:18:04.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho Kaizuka, Milady?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.45,0:18:08.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kaizuka...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.55,0:18:28.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.82,0:18:34.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Er, no... Look, aren't those flowers lovely, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.19,0:18:40.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is Dales Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.65,0:18:44.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Currently closing on enemy\NLanding Castle with Orlov Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.32,0:18:45.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Clydesdale Platoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.29,0:18:55.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The arrowheads are equipped with \Na powerful explosive charge! Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.87,0:18:58.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.96,0:19:05.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't waste your ammunition!\NThe enemy is cloaked and fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.72,0:19:07.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The bow seems to be its weapon,\Nwhich is probably to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.13,0:19:12.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, muzzle flashes would make\Nit easy to pinpoint its location.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.51,0:19:13.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This must be to avoid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.96,0:19:17.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Optical camouflage?\NThey have cloaking technology?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.35,0:19:18.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The device's based on that, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.85,0:19:21.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's more ingenious than just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.52,0:19:26.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing on my thermograph,\Nand it's not casting a shadow. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.28,0:19:28.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's definitely out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.70,0:19:29.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.08,0:19:35.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are giving this\Nto me, Milord?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.45,0:19:39.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Customize it however you like.\NI've already discussed the matters
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.71,0:19:41.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of your peerage title and activation\Nfactor with Princess Lemrina.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.46,0:19:44.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Slaine...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.00,0:19:48.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The arrow has been loosed.\NThere is no turning back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.76,0:19:49.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milord!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.43,0:19:54.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inform Count Sebring, \NCount Raffia, and Count Orga
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.68,0:19:56.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that they are to prove their fealty to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.90,0:20:04.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Smoke grenades, loading complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.03,0:20:05.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ready here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.15,0:20:10.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fire!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.17,0:20:29.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's right. It's definitely out there.\NAnd if it is...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.09,0:20:32.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...it will have an effect on air currents!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.98,0:20:40.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Target located.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.23,0:20:42.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Open fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.23,0:20:43.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lieutenant!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.48,0:20:44.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.11,0:20:46.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At our 3 o'clock! New enemy!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.33,0:20:58.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,New enemy closing in from dead ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.20,0:21:01.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're attacking as a team?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.21,0:21:03.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}From overhead, too! Incoming!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.05,0:21:12.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Landing Castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.47,0:21:14.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All units, brace for impact!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.66,0:21:44.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Multiple Landing Castles...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.87,0:21:46.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Multiple Kataphrakts...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.25,0:21:48.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Simultaneously!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.71,0:21:52.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's making his move!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.97,0:21:54.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's him!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.72,0:21:58.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right. It's too late for doubts now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.10,0:22:03.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is no returning from\Nthis place I have come to.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.05,0:22:10.05,T1,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Flaw in Paradise
